(155, 'AAMkADdmZGY1MTVlLWQ1NTYtNGI0Ni05NjNiLTJlMjRjZWY3NDI0MQBGAAAAAADWV5v5kSGKT7AyRKAqenxDBwDufhLbsaXjSapBeAPWsZVWAAAAAAEMAADufhLbsaXjSapBeAPWsZVWAAAUpXRjAAA=', 'AAQkADdmZGY1MTVlLWQ1NTYtNGI0Ni05NjNiLTJlMjRjZWY3NDI0MQAQAJPplZ4PCvNKl0-3DXkLcIU=', 'hibernianusers@hibernianhealth.com', 'alan.moran@hibernianhealth.com', '', '', 'i4Life ', '<html><head>\r\n<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\"><meta name=\"Generator\" content=\"Microsoft Word 15 (filtered medium)\"><style>\r\n<!--\r\n@font-face\r\n	{font-family:Wingdings}\r\n@font-face\r\n	{font-family:\"Angsana New\"}\r\n@font-face\r\n	{font-family:\"Cambria Math\"}\r\n@font-face\r\n	{font-family:Calibri}\r\n@font-face\r\n	{font-family:Tahoma}\r\n@font-face\r\n	{font-family:\"Leelawadee UI\"}\r\n@font-face\r\n	{font-family:\"Century Gothic\"}\r\np.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\r\n	{margin:0cm;\r\n	font-size:11.0pt;\r\n	font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif}\r\nspan.EmailStyle18\r\n	{font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;\r\n	color:windowtext}\r\nspan.EmailStyle19\r\n	{font-family:\"Calibri\",sans-serif;\r\n	color:windowtext}\r\n.MsoChpDefault\r\n	{font-size:10.0pt}\r\n@page WordSection1\r\n	{margin:72.0pt 72.0pt 72.0pt 72.0pt}\r\ndiv.WordSection1\r\n	{}\r\nol\r\n	{margin-bottom:0cm}\r\nul\r\n	{margin-bottom:0cm}\r\n-->\r\n</style></head><body lang=\"EN-IE\" link=\"#0563C1\" vlink=\"#954F72\" style=\"word-wrap:break-word\"><div class=\"WordSection1\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"\">Hello Everyone,<br>Dr Kevin Connolly, Medical Adviser for all our vaccination training programmes, helped set up an Irish charity in 2010 to tackle the child malnutrition problem in the Linda Compound in Lusaka, Zambia. Yana and myself are just back from a week with the i4Life team where we saw first-hand the incredible work they are doing. The local team and Irish volunteers provide nutrition training and medical care to mothers and children. The team includes Community Health Workers (CHWs) who live locally and are so good at encouraging new mothers to engage. The average age of new mothers presenting at the clinic is 12-15 which presents its own healthcare problems for mother and baby. The programmes i4Life deliver are designed by nutritionists and doctors and they have a strong clinical and operational governance framework to protect the children in their care.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"\">&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"\">One of the most impressive features of the set-up is the way the team supports and enables the CHWs who live in the community. The team are trained and mentored to support pregnant women and new mothers to provide adequate pre and post-natal nutrition. <br>Everyone gets fed when they come to the nutrition clinic and Yana was given a lesson in preparing Nshima by Mary! Its maize based and it can be like sticky rice or softer like porridge with vegetables added. Also, while we were in country, we met the Irish Aid officer and the Irish Ambassador, Brona Carr, who welcomed us to her private residence and was very supportive of the i4Life mission. The new Irish Aid plan for the future is very closely aligned to the i4Life model so I hope they will get plenty of support as they expand.<br><br>Were delighted to support i4Life as our charity partner and were doing a couple of practical things to help:</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"\">&nbsp;</span></p><ul type=\"disc\" style=\"margin-top:0cm\"><li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><span style=\"\">The team were sharing a vehicle which restricted their outreach to the outskirts of the compound so we sponsored a Toyota 4 wheel drive to provide transport</span></li><li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><span style=\"\">i4Life encourage medics and nutritionists from Ireland as well as Zambia to do placements in the clinic. Due to space constraints, training has to be done outside. Weve sponsored a new education centre to be built in the community which will focus on providing space for the CHWs and visiting medics to complete their assignments. We turned the sod on the site when we were over and its hoped to start construction after the rainy season.</span></li><li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><span style=\"\">Education is a very important part of our business  educating patients, HCPS, pharmacists, first responders etc so we could see where some of our expertise in e-learning could be used to support the team on the ground. Yana is building e-learning with the Department of Food Science &amp; Nutrition at UNZA which will be cascaded to support the community teams. The model i4Life employs means that the cascading of knowledge is a key element so we will be trying to get micro learning to the CHWs as part of their ongoing mentoring. </span></li></ul><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"\">&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"\">I hope we will be supporting fundraising for this really worthy charity  run by volunteer CEO Maura Moran (no relation!) and team  and when we have some news on activities, Ill be asking you to consider supporting i4Life in whatever way you can. If you have any ideas on running a fundraising event, wed love to hear.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"\"><br>Please see <a href=\"https://i4Life.ie\">https://i4Life.ie</a> .</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"\">&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"\">Thanks,</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"\">Alan</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"\">&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"\">&nbsp;</span></p><div><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt; font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif; color:#1F497D\">Alan Moran</span></b><span style=\"\"></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:10.0pt; font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif; color:#1F497D\">Group Managing Director</span><span s